r share. [...] Read more about Zimmer Biomet here.\\n\\n## Pfizer\\n\\nDrug manufacturer Pfizer rounds out our list of best healthcare stocks to buy. Pfizer is one of the world’s largest pharmaceutical firms, with annual sales of roughly $60 billion. The stock is 31% undervalued relative to our fair value estimate of $36 per share.\\n\\nPfizer’s foundation remains solid, based on steady cash flows generated from a basket of diverse drugs. The company’s large size confers significant competitive advantages in developing new drugs. This heft, combined with a broad portfolio of patent-protected drugs, has helped Pfizer build an economic moat around its business.", "score": 0.8674071}, {"title": "Best Healthcare Stocks to Buy in 2026 and How to Invest in Them", "url": "https://www.fool.com/investing/stock-market/market-sectors/healthcare/", "content": "Follow us\\n\\n## Key Points\\n\\n Healthcare stocks represent companies in a growing sector, crucial as global spending is high.\\n Top firms like UnitedHealth and Vertex Pharmaceuticals lead in market stability and innovation.\\n Investment in healthcare is strategic due to an aging population and technology advances.\\n\\nEverybody needs healthcare -- or will, at some point. And, when there’s something everyone needs, there’s a huge opportunity for investors. Healthcare stocks are shares of publicly traded companies that provide healthcare products or services. [...] Ticker Information Table\\n\\n| Name and ticker | Current price | Market cap | Industry |\\n| Vertex Pharmaceuticals (NASDAQ:VRTX) | $454.00 | $115.3 billion | Biotechnology |\\n| Intuitive Surgical (NASDAQ:ISRG) | $477.94 | $169.7 billion | Healthcare Equipment and Supplies |\\n| TransMedics Group (NASDAQ:TMDX) | $113.90 | $3.9 billion | Healthcare Equipment and Supplies |\\n| UnitedHealth Group (NYSE:UNH) | $275.59 | $250.1 billion | Healthcare Providers and Services |\\n| HCA Healthcare (NYSE:HCA) | $493.71 | $110.4 billion | Healthcare Providers and Services |\\n| Cardinal Health (NYSE:CAH) | $208.08 | $48.9 billion | Healthcare Providers and Services |\\n\\nData as of Mar 21, 2026. Showing 6of6tickers.\\n\\n## 1. Vertex Pharmaceuticals\\n\\n## NASDAQ: VRTX\\n\\nVertex Pharmaceuticals\\n\\nToday\'s Change [...] ## 4. UnitedHealth Group\\n\\nUnitedHealth Group (UNH -1.73%) is the largest commercial health insurer in the U.S. It also operates one of the biggest pharmacy benefit managers (PBMs) and is a leader in healthcare delivery services. The company’s size, stability, and dividend make UnitedHealth Group one of the most attractive payer stocks on the market. UnitedHealth Group has also expanded its presence in the healthcare provider market with its 2023 acquisition of home health services provider LHC Group.\\n\\n## 5. HCA Healthcare", "score": 0.852752}, {"title": "Best Health Insurance Stocks for 2026 and How to Invest", "url": "https://www.fool.com/investing/stock-market/market-sectors/financials/insurance-stocks/health-insurance-stocks/", "content": "## Top health insurance stocks for 2026\\n\\nHere are four publicly traded health insurance companies likely to perform well over the long term:\\n\\nTicker Information Table\\n\\n| Name and ticker | Current price | Market cap | Dividend yield |\\n| UnitedHealth Group (NYSE:UNH) | $293.40 | $265.6 billion | 2.98% |\\n| Elevance Health (NYSE:ELV) | $346.80 | $76.5 billion | 1.97% |\\n| CVS Health (NYSE:CVS) | $78.42 | $99.8 billion | 3.39% |\\n| Centene (NYSE:CNC) | $40.52 | $19.9 billion | 0.00% |\\n\\nData as of Feb 14, 2026. Showing 4of4tickers.\\n\\n## 1. UnitedHealth Group\\n\\n## NYSE: UNH\\n\\nUnitedHealth Group\\n\\nToday\'s Change\\n\\n(3.17%) $9.03\\n\\nCurrent Price\\n\\n$293.40\\n\\n### Key Data Points\\n\\nMarket Cap\\n\\n$266B\\n\\nDay\'s Range\\n\\n$284.65- $293.46\\n\\n52wk Range\\n\\n$234.60- $606.36\\n\\nVolume\\n\\n441K\\n\\nAvg Vol\\n\\n8.8M\\n\\nDividend Yield\\n\\n2.98% [...] Volume\\n\\n441K\\n\\nAvg Vol\\n\\n8.8M\\n\\nDividend Yield\\n\\n2.98%\\n\\nUnitedHealth Group (UNH +3.17%) ranks as the biggest health insurer in the world by far. Its UnitedHealthcare business unit offers health plans for employers and individuals. It\'s also a major player in the markets for Medicare Advantage, Medicare supplemental plans, and Medicaid.\\n\\nThe company\'s Optum business segment provides information- and technology-enabled health services, including OptumRx pharmacy benefits management (PBM) services. While UnitedHealthcare generates around three-fourths of the company’s total revenue, Optum has been a key growth driver for UnitedHealth Group in the past. [...] ## Health insurance stock FAQ\\n\\n### About the Author\\n\\nKeith Speights is a contributing Motley Fool healthcare analyst covering publicly traded companies across pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, medical devices, technology, and marijuana. Prior to The Motley Fool, Keith was CEO of Constant Care Technology, a healthcare technology company; vice president of American HealthTech, a healthcare software company; and a director of operations for Blue Cross Blue Shield of Mississippi, a health insurer. He holds a B.S. in Industrial Engineering from Mississippi State University.\\n\\nKeith Speights has no position in any of the stocks mentioned. The Motley Fool recommends CVS Health and UnitedHealth Group. The Motley Fool has a disclosure policy.\\n\\n### Stocks Mentioned\\n\\n#### Elevance Health\\n\\nNYSE: ELV", "score": 0.8232293}, {"title": "9 Best-Performing Health Care Stocks for March 2026 - NerdWallet", "url": "https://www.nerdwallet.com/investing/learn/best-performing-healthcare-stocks", "content": "37.36%\\n\\nMCK\\n\\nMckesson Corporation\\n\\n33.64%\\n\\nGILD\\n\\nGilead Sciences, Inc\\n\\n29.91%\\n\\nSource: Finviz. Data is current as of March 20, 2026, and is intended for informational purposes only.\\n\\n» Ready to start investing? See our picks for the best brokers for stock trading\\n\\n| Brokerage firms |  |\\n --- |\\n|  |  |\\n|  |  |\\